Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Install Python and pytest
    apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-pip && \
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------ #
    # Prepare initial filesystem state for the exercise
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------ #

    # Create required directories
    mkdir -p /home/user/datasets

    # Create the raw_records.log file with exact required content
    cat > /home/user/datasets/raw_records.log <<'EOF'
ABC123 SUCCESS Data loaded
DEF456 FAILURE Data missing
XYZ789 SUCCESS Completed
abc111 SUCCESS lowercase
123ABC SUCCESS misplaced
LMN000 SUCCESS component
NOP999 FAULT unexpected
QRS321 SUCCESS processed
TUV654 DEFER waiting
GHI777 SUCCESS final
EOF

    # Set appropriate permissions
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user/datasets
    chmod 644 /home/user/datasets/raw_records.log

%labels
    Author      container-builder
    Description Environment for log filtering task with pytest installed.

%help
This container provides the starting point for the log-filtering task.
It supplies:
  • /home/user/datasets/raw_records.log with the exact required content.
  • pytest installed for automated testing.
No /home/user/clean_data directory exists so the student can create it as part
of the solution.